 method 
 In   case the mouth is closed tightly,   use Schafer’s or 
Holgen-Nelson method. 
 Treatment for electrical burns 
 A person receiving an electric shock may also sustain 
burns when the current passes through the body. 
Do not waste time by rendering first aid to the 
victim until breathing has been restored and 
the patient can breathe normally unaided. 
Burns are very painful. Ifa large area of the body is burnt, 
do not give treatment, except to exclude the air, eg. by 
covering with clean paper ora clean cloth, soaked in clean 
water. this relieves the pain. 
Severe bleeding 
 Any wound which is bleeding profusely, especially in the 
 wrist,   hand or fingers must be considered serious and 
must receive professional attention. 
Immediate action 
Always in cases of severe bleeding 
-   make the patient to lle down and rest 
-   if possible, raise the injured part above the level of the 
body (Fig 1) 
-   apply pressure to the wound 
-   callfor medical assistance 
To control severe bleeding 
Squeeze together the sides of the wound. Apply pressure 
as long as it is necessary to stop the bleeding. When the 
bleeding has stopped, put a dressing over the wound and 
cover it with a pad of soft material. (Fig 2) 
