Necessity of measuring the wire sizes 
A proper estimate involves determination of current in 
different loads, correct selection of the type of cable, size 
of the cable and the required quantity. Any error will result 
indefective wiring, fire accidents and bring unhappinesste 
both the house owner and the electrician. 
Asound knowledge about the area of the cross-sectionof 
the core, the diameter   ofthe single strand of the conductor 
andthe number of conductors in each core of the stranded 
conductor is essential for a wiremanto be successful in his 
carreer. 
